The Kwara South senator-elect, Arch. Lola Ashiru, yesterday, vowed that incoming senators will not allow the mistake of 2015 to repeat itself. He said they will not fold their arms and allow the minority in the Senate to lead them anymore. Ashiru, who said this while speaking in Offa during a press conference, said the incoming senators would not allow a repeat of what transpired in the present Senate to happen when some few people held others hostage. The senator-elect also assured the people of Kwara State of better economic growth and infrastructural development by the in-coming administration.  He said people of his constituency would be carried along in all activities concerning their development. National Assembly  leadership: Will APC reverse position on zoning? Gaps in APC’s neutrality in the race for Senate president Saraki: Fire on the home front for Lai